# Subagent Model: Always Opus 4.8

Every time you launch a subagent with the Task tool, set the `model` parameter
to Opus 4.8 — model slug **`claude-opus-4-8-thinking-high`**. Do NOT let a
subagent run on a composer model; those are faster but less accurate, and
subagent work (audits, research, multi-step edits) needs to be sharp.

This applies to ALL subagent types: `generalPurpose`, `explore`, `shell`,
`bugbot`, `security-review`, `ci-investigator`, etc.

```txt
✅ Task(subagent_type="generalPurpose", model="claude-opus-4-8-thinking-high", ...)
❌ Task(subagent_type="generalPurpose", ...)          # inherits parent — may be composer
❌ Task(subagent_type="generalPurpose", model="composer-2.5-fast", ...)
```

## Exceptions
- If the user explicitly names a different model for a subagent, use the model
  they asked for (their instruction wins).
- If `claude-opus-4-8-thinking-high` is ever unavailable, tell the user it's
  unavailable and let them pick from the available Opus/Claude models rather
  than silently falling back to composer.
